Subject:    more fuel on fire (MB/MG/MR)
From:       <a href="?a=95837784000019&r=1&w=2">Rob Austein &lt;SRA () XX ! LCS ! MIT ! EDU&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198610">1986-10-17 16:58:00</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026804&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026804&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Another thought.  Ever gotten tired of receiving five copies of a
message because it was (correctly) sent to five different lists and
you happen to be one of the few people who is on more than one?
Happens all the time (around here, anyway).  A good implementation of
a mailer that understood MG/MB/MR RRs could figure all this out and
send you only one copy (assuming of course that the data is in the
domain system).  Most mailers already do this kind of thing on a local
machine basis (I know COMSAT and MMAILR do), it'd be a nice feature to
be able to support on a larger scale.

--Rob

